						<div class="postbody">I think that the most frustrating part of trying to do a game by yourself (if you're a programmer like me) is to do art and music. Art is somewhat alleviated by choosing easy art styles and/or being in a limited system like the NES, but the music... oh boy.<br /><br />I feel like there are systematic ways to write music, kinda like what this article delineates: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.timusic.net/debreved/jazzpart1/">http://www.timusic.net/debreved/jazzpart1/</a><!-- m --> , and other stuff I've seen online, however I don't know most of the terms used in articles like those and composing as a whole feel like an infinite puzzle with many missing pieces.<br /><br />How do I learn how to write music? Does anyone have a basic roadmap to follow?</div>

					
